In sum, despite the progressive‑rock candidate being album‑oriented and including extended tracks, its specific attributes—clear vocal placement, preserved dynamics, hook emphasis, tasteful arrangements, and purposeful sequencing—match my stated likes much more closely and avoid the production pitfalls I dislike. The 'Memphis' listing lacks the production and sequencing details I require to endorse it, so I reject it in favor of the progressive‑rock CD.

